column3: Automatic sanity-testing: PASSED, see http://jenkins.bluematt.me/pull-tester/p4568_9c347313f7f504d602a9d744f1ad7aee4e3d6f9a/ for binaries and test log.\nThis test script verifies pulls every time they are updated. It, however, dies sometimes and fails to test properly.  If you are waiting on a test, please check timestamps to verify that the test.log is moving at http://jenkins.bluematt.me/pull-te
This change has been tested extensively.  It has been deployed and exercised on mainnet since 2014-05-22.\n
It sounds like a useful addition, however I don't like to add dead code. Are there any places in the current code where this could be used?\n
@laanwj I just broke it out because you mentioned it.  No problem if you want to close this or set it aside.\n
Yes I still think it makes sense API-wise. And you add a test. So ACK.\n
